     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>To the Booke.</head>
   <lg>
      <l>RIch mine of Art: Minnion of Mercury;</l>
      <l>True Truch-man of the mind of Mystery</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Inuentions storehouse; Nymph of Helicon:</l>
      <l>Deepe Moralist of Times tradition:</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Vnto this Paragon of Brutus race</l>
      <l>Present thy seruice, and with cheerefull grace</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Say (if Pythagoras beleeu'd may bee)</l>
      <l>The soule of <hi>ancient Wisedome</hi> liues in the</l>
   </lg>
</div>
